# 10. 希望をつなげて

Minori: Wow...
Minori: It's been so long since Chi last sent me a message!
Airi: Chi...? Isn't she the person you've mentioned to us like a hundred times? The one you went to see that ASRUN show with?
Minori: Yeah! She's trying to become a dancer and is training overseas right now!
KAITO: Wow, overseas...?!
Minori: We haven't been able to talk much since we've both been really busy. I wonder why she decided to contact me now...
Minori: Oh...
Haruka: Is something wrong?
Minori: <I saw the show you were on via that station's streaming service. I've actually been feeling kind of down after something that happened recently...>
Minori: <But seeing you really cheered me up. That's why I'm sending you this message. To thank you.> ...is what she wrote!
Shizuku: That's so wonderful. Even though she's overseas, she was still able to see us on that show.
Haruka: Yeah, also... It sounds like you were able to give her just the encouragement she was looking for, Minori.
Haruka: I'm so happy for you.
Minori: Thanks...
Minori: Hearing from her like this also makes me really happy!
Len: Oh, here comes the not-rain again...
Minori: Look! Those flower buds are blooming now!
Rin: Wow, you're right...! Do you think it's because of the rain?
KAITO: What if these raindrops represent all the hope you've spread to others, or the thoughts and feelings of all those people...?
Shizuku: Huh?
KAITO: I can't say for certain...
KAITO: But I have a feeling that it started raining because Minori was able to cheer Chi up.
KAITO: And this flower is a symbol of hope because it's being watered by this rain...
KAITO: In other words, spreading hope to Chi caused this flower to bloom.
Minori: Oh...
Len: I have to agree.
Len: This rain has this warmth to it. The kind of warmth I feel whenever I'm watching you girls perform on stage.
Len: If these flowers represent everyone's thoughts and feelings, then it makes sense how touching them allows you to see what they're thinking.
MEIKO: I'm sure the reason why they're this beautiful is because they've been nurtured by your gentle warmth.
Luka: Hehe. What a lovely thought.
Luka: Which means, to borrow what KAITO just said, we can call these “flowers of hope”.
Haruka: Flowers of hope...?
Rin: Oh, I really like that!
MEIKO: But this field... Most of the flowers in it are still just buds.
KAITO: Which means it's going to look incredibly beautiful once they've all bloomed. Imagine all the colors we're going to see.
Minori: All the colors...
Minori: That's it...!
Haruka: Minori?
Minori: I just realized something amazing...!
Miku: Amazing?
Minori: See that stage over there? I just realized that the view from up there would look a lot like...
Minori: A lot like the glowsticks everyone's going to be waving around when we do our show at the Dome!
Haruka: So, this place appeared because we were able to come up with a concrete goal for ourselves and it's a sign of us making progress toward achieving it?
Airi: Dunno... But by the time all the flowers here are in full bloom...
Airi: We might be at a point in our careers as idols where we can actually do a show at the Dome.
Minori: Wow...!
Minori: We gotta keep doing our best.
Minori: We gotta keep spreading hope to everyone, make all these flowers bloom...!
Minori: And do a show at the Dome someday.
Minori: When we do, we'll get to see a big, beautiful field of glowsticks waving around!
Haruka: Yeah, let's keep doing our best.
Shizuku: Yes, let's!
Miku: (MORE MORE JUMP! is such an incredible group.)
Miku: (Initially, everything had come to a standstill for them. They were all broken, bruised or scarred in some way...)
Miku: (But they were all able to connect around the idea of spreading and inspiring hope in others. That's what allowed them to stand back up and pursue their dreams.)
Miku: (And now, they're beginning to spread hope to the wider masses.)
Airi: Anyway, with that out of the way, we need to start polishing our stream ideas for tomorrow's meeting.
Minori: Oh, that's right!
Minori: Fortunately, I feel like I know what I want to do now after getting a chance to see everyone's thoughts...!
Haruka: Me too... I have a good feeling about the ideas I'll be bringing with me.
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm looking forward to hearing what you all came up with tomorrow.
Rin: Huh...? What's this...?
Len: What's what?
Rin: This... It looks like a little sprout.
Luka: Oh, you're right... And it looks a bit different from all the flowers around here.
KAITO: Yes, but...
KAITO: I have a feeling that this sprout will get bigger and bigger alongside you girls.
KAITO: In that sense... I'm looking forward to seeing how it grows.
Shizuku: Right. I'm already getting excited about seeing what kind of flower it blossoms into!
Haruka: We can't say for sure that it's going to turn into a flower.
Airi: We'll just have to stay tuned to find out. In any case, we're going to do everything we can to make all the flowers in the field bloom!
Minori: Yeah!
Minori: Alright, so that we get to perform at the Dome someday! Ready, everyone?!
Minori: MORE MORE...
Shizuku, Airi & Haruka: JUMP!
